replies.body:
First off, I wanted to mention that I **am not** part of the eSports team, so the following is purely my thoughts on the subject.

Running it similarly to the LCS will be pretty tough since the tournament client isn't something that's publicly available. The best format I could think of would be to have the players in a separate room from the audience and livestream with the delay. Just throw some content in there to hold the audience over until the stream catches up. Maybe you could do a raffle or a trivia game, or maybe you could take a vote from the audience on who they think will win the matchup.

I hope this helps! {{sticker:slayer-pantheon-thumbs}}
